   journal = {Social Cognitive and Affective Neuroscience},
   keywords = {Decision making,FMRI,IBMA,Meta-analysis,Value},
   note = {Meta-analysis to answer 4 questions: Q1) Overall SV correlates in the brain? A: vmPFC, VS, and PCC; Q2) Can these regions be subdivided into networks? A: &quot;this region of VMPFC is divided into subregions that co-activate with different networks: one that involves central VMPFC, dorsal dPCC and VSTR, and another that involves more anterior VMPFC, left ANG and vPCC.”; Q3) Decision vs outcome? A: vmPFC + VS, with the addition of dPCC for decision; and Q4) Separable by reward modality? A: monetary has vmPFC and VS, but food didn't show VS (odd, but maybe due to money being stronger)<br/><br/><br/>Results are mostly congruent with Bartra et al 2013. Novelty: 1) vmPFC centroids differentially co-activate with other brain areas, with anterior being more DN-like; 2) concrete-to-abstract value computation gradient in vmPFC follows a posterior-to-anterior organization. Also, no ACC/dmPFC.},
