   note = {Regression using ICA-based individualized rsFC maps (98 pp) as predictors can reproduce idiosyncratic activity patterns on most HCP tasks<br/><br/>For all tasks, predicted and actual maps were more similar within-subject vs either a median-map or across individuals. This is even though &quot;the prediction was more similar to the map it had not seen (subject X) than to the maps it had seen (all but subject X)&quot; (leave-one-out model fit/eval)<br/><br/>Model can predict where, to what extent, and in which hemisphere actual activation will occur.<br/><br/>The model can properly predict atypical activations in never before seen subjects (e.g. lack of activity in an area where the average subject shows activity)},
