   journal = {Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America},
   note = {adding fixation bias to the DDM in a way that compares the evidence for best vs next best allows for a good model expansion from binary to trinary value-based choices. <br/><br/>fitting trinary with binary-fit parameters works, suggesting a generalizable mechanism for choices<br/><br/>the model provides a good fit to choice and RT data, a better fit than relying on item value alone, and better fit than a similar best vs avg model.},
